Temporary Post!! But, What do you think about this Video? 

Times are sure getting stranger and stranger by the second. All of this Artificial intelligence (A.I) and the way they use technology is definitely scary Now. It’s giving Black Mirror.

This isn’t a “Summer Body” This is MY BODY!!! 

If you’re going to set goals for yourself. You MUST do what’s necessary in order to achieve those goals. That includes cutting out ALL BULLSHIT. Anything that isn’t serving you in a good way; Mentally or Physically will never allow you to flourish and thrive. 

Eat, Drink and Live in a  Bullshit mindset or lifestyle, Get Bullshit Results…. If you want it WORK FOR IT! It ain’t No secrets. No shortcuts. Quick fixes. 

Be Disciplined 
Workout
EAT ACCORDING TO YOUR GOALS
It’s just that simple. 

Some days I’m Slim. Some days I’m “Thick” Everyday I LOVE MYSELF at any Phase my body may transition into. I’m a Daily Work in progress. Give yourself grace but, keep working on the best version of yourself for YOURSELF. 💪🏽 YOU GOT THIS. Nobody said this Journey would be easy but, trust it’s all worth it. 
“When you Love your Body. You project Self-Confidence” 
I Love me some Me…. Love you some YOU!! 

#NicB #Getfitwithnic #getfitwithnic_ #Body #SelfLove #Wellness #Healthy #nicbfitlife #nicbfit

One things for certain and 2 things For Sure. I am going to Exercise for the rest of my life. I am fully committed to Wellness. I may take a break here and there. Eat a little crap from time to time but, it’s never for long.

STILL THAT GIRL!! Always gon be THAT GIRL!

BEFORE: OCT 22 BETWEEN 5’4 160-165lbs 
AFTER: SEPT 20TH 23 5’4 137Lb 

165lb is the heaviest I’ve ever been in my life and as mentioned before I loved the Thickness on me. But, because of my height it was just too much for me. My knees were in so much Pain.🥴

I purposely wore the same exact outfit yesterday. Only because I really wanted to see and show you all the difference in my Shape. 

How Did I Do it? 

I stopped drinking alcohol (9 1/2 No Alcohol) I drink Mocktails or Sparkling water with a Lime when I’m out. 
I eat according to my goals. 
CHANGE YOUR DIET! You can’t eat crap and expect to get results!!! 
I drink about 6 bottles of water daily (16.9oz)
I workout at least 4Xs a Week for 40mins. Depending on how many clients I have in a day. I do more. 
When I don’t have much time I incorporate a quick 10Min Routine in my bedroom that consists of:
1 Min Squats
5 Min Jog In Place
2 Min Jumping Jacks
1 Min Plank 
1 Min Squat Punches

No matter what shape or size I’m at. I’m will continue to Work on becoming the Best Version of myself. No matter if it’s 135lbs or 165lbs. I love and embrace every inch of this natural body. You don’t get results over night Unless you’re doing bullshit to your body. And that comes with a price in the end. So, do it the right way. Learn your body. Love your body. YOU CAN DO IT!!

Once you begin to excel to another level in your Personal Development. You become one of the most Powerful being. It’s like nothing can faze you….So, ain’t nobody got no business asking me. “WHO I THINK I AM.” 

I AM WHOEVER I WANT and CHOOSE TO BE!

I Am THIS and I Am THAT. Whatever that looks like to me. Nobody can define Who I think I am. 

Don’t insult me asking me no stupid sh*t! lmao 

Just Be YOU and DO YOU.
